      "OK, this is in `reql_admin` as of 406eb98ab994215066cdc5f022bd698064515e13. There is a field called `cache_size_mb` in `rethinkdb.server_config` which can be set to a positive real number of megabytes or to `\"auto\"`. In addition, the user can pass a `--cache-size` parameter, which overrides the stored value; its value can be an integer number of megabytes or the word `auto`. The actual cache size in use is still in `rethinkdb.server_status` in the same place."
